isn't the special act.

00:32:54.952 --> 00:32:56.162
Or the Special Committee.

00:32:57.789 --> 00:32:58.706
It's me.

00:33:05.171 --> 00:33:06.756
Isn't that why you did it?

00:33:06.839 --> 00:33:07.882
Darn it.

00:33:08.633 --> 00:33:10.843
I don't get what you're trying to say.

00:33:11.969 --> 00:33:15.389
You thought I'd get released
if Ms. Sung got to the police station.

00:33:16.057 --> 00:33:19.477
You want me to be the culprit
more than anyone else does.

00:33:19.560 --> 00:33:21.521
You must've planned to bury the act

00:33:21.604 --> 00:33:24.148
with the news
that I was the hit-and-run offender.

00:33:24.232 --> 00:33:26.275
Isn't that why you did

00:33:27.652 --> 00:33:30.154
such a horrible thing to Ms. Sung?

00:33:31.989 --> 00:33:35.743
Gosh, my sister is so quick to catch on.

00:33:36.410 --> 00:33:37.578
So why did you do it?

00:33:38.830 --> 00:33:39.705
What?

00:33:42.083 --> 00:33:46.420
A paternity test or whatever, I told you
not to do anything, but you ignored it.

00:33:46.504 --> 00:33:48.965
Why didn't you do as I said
and make things worse?

00:33:50.675 --> 00:33:54.387
If you keep acting out of place,
what will happen next?

00:33:54.971 --> 00:33:56.097
The news reports

00:33:56.722 --> 00:33:58.474
different accidents every day.

00:33:58.558 --> 00:34:00.226
But you know what?

00:34:00.309 --> 00:34:03.396
There's no such thing
as an accident that happens by chance.

00:34:04.188 --> 00:34:06.566
If they knew
why they got into the accidents,

00:34:06.649 --> 00:34:09.235
they wouldn't feel wronged at least,
you know?

00:34:09.318 --> 00:34:10.736
You're threatening me again?

00:34:10.820 --> 00:34:11.946
I'm giving you

00:34:12.029 --> 00:34:14.657
a heads-up so that you won't feel wronged.

00:34:15.449 --> 00:34:17.243
You won't feel wronged too, then.

00:34:17.326 --> 00:34:18.870
What?

00:34:18.953 --> 00:34:20.454
What you can do,

00:34:21.164 --> 00:34:22.623
I can do as well.

00:34:28.462 --> 00:34:30.131
It's not difficult.

00:34:30.214 --> 00:34:32.842
You just need to open the door.

00:34:33.426 --> 00:34:37.763
Then Senior Inspector Jung
will go in and drag everyone out.

00:34:37.847 --> 00:34:39.140
So,

00:34:39.223 --> 00:34:42.977
make sure you go with Min-cheol
when he goes inside to negotiate.

00:34:43.060 --> 00:34:45.104
So you can open the door.

00:34:45.813 --> 00:34:47.273
You know the Trojan Horse, right?

00:34:47.356 --> 00:34:48.274
MARCH 2012

00:34:48.357 --> 00:34:51.777
It isn't anything difficult,
but your role is very important.

00:34:52.361 --> 00:34:53.905
You must be very pressed.

00:34:54.947 --> 00:34:57.408
You, who chairs the sponsorship
for Jeong-yeon,

00:34:57.491 --> 00:34:59.202
are asking for my help.

00:35:01.787 --> 00:35:02.997
I am pressed.

00:35:03.080 --> 00:35:05.583
It's been more than three months

00:35:05.666 --> 00:35:08.294
since they locked up the factory
and started protesting.

00:35:08.377 --> 00:35:10.296
Father is rushing me to resolve it.

00:35:10.379 --> 00:35:11.505
And my younger brother

00:35:12.465 --> 00:35:16.469
is brown-nosing my father
and saying I'm not competent enough.

00:35:16.552 --> 00:35:18.346
I'm in a serious bind.

00:35:20.097 --> 00:35:21.015
You'll help me, right?

00:35:22.099 --> 00:35:23.267
Why would I?

00:35:25.770 --> 00:35:27.647
The election is around the corner,

00:35:28.648 --> 00:35:30.483
but you're losing to Cha Jeong-yeon.

00:35:31.275 --> 00:35:32.652
Will you lose the election?

00:35:32.735 --> 00:35:34.111
I'll help you win.

00:35:34.195 --> 00:35:35.363
You will?

00:35:37.198 --> 00:35:38.324
How?

00:35:42.662 --> 00:35:43.913
Cha Jeong-yeon…

00:35:45.414 --> 00:35:47.208
has an illegal election committee.

00:35:48.709 --> 00:35:52.255
And Senior Inspector Jung here
runs the election committee.

00:35:52.338 --> 00:35:55.049
He's a jack of all trades, you see.

00:35:55.132 --> 00:35:58.719
Just get the reporters ready.
I'll help them catch them in the act.

00:35:58.803 --> 00:36:01.722
Then Cha Jeong-yeon's approval rating
will plummet.

00:36:02.598 --> 00:36:04.976
Who'd vote for the one who'd be taken down

00:36:05.059 --> 00:36:07.645
for violating the election act
even if he won?

00:36:08.646 --> 00:36:11.399
Their vote is the only thing
the people have,

00:36:11.482 --> 00:36:14.694
and they can't stand
their votes going to waste.

00:36:17.571 --> 00:36:22.159
Did you chair his sponsorship committee
and provide him with manpower

00:36:22.243 --> 00:36:23.786
for a moment like this?

00:36:24.745 --> 00:36:26.414
